gomodel:SYNGO_1445  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099059 replaced by GO:0048787" , "Rationale: Immuno gold labeling of alpha subunit of BK channel\n\n21/11/2017 Pim\n- Literal: \"Taken together, these results indicate that BK channel α-subunits are targeted to the presynaptic active zone of hippocampal glutamatergic synapses.\"\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chose.. Experimental description: Subjects. Male Wistar rats (Möllegaard, Ejby, Denmark) were deeply anesthetized with halothane before decapitation or fixation. Adult rats (6-10 weeks old) were used for morphological studies; 4- to 6-week-old rats were used for electrophysiology experiments. The care and use of animals were in accordance with institutional guidelines." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9425-2935" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1445" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

